Nightmare mudlib living lfun: add_skill()

int add_skill(string type, int level, int train, float max)

string type - the skill to add
int level - the current level of skill
int train - the amount of xp trained for skill
float max - the per level tier max

This adds a new skill called "type" with a current level of "level" with a set trained xp of "train" with a set tier max.   
If this skill already exists in the object, then nothing happens and a 0 is returned.  
A 1 is returned in the case of success.

See also: query_all_skills(), set_skill()
Defined in /std/living/skills.c
